frege.rt

Class Product7<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,T7>

  • java.lang.Object
    • frege.rt.Product7<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,T7>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Value

    public abstract class Product7<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,T7>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Value

    Base class for values constructed with 7-ary constructors.

    This will be extended by constructors of sum types and by product types. Subclasses must implement the Value._c() method and the Lazy interface.

    Note that Product7 is not a subclass of Product6!

    • Method Detail

      • _c

        public abstract int _c()

        Must be implemented by subclasses to return their constructor number.

        Specified by:
        _c in interface Value
        Returns:
        the zero based constructor number for values of algebraic data types, or 0 for native types and functions.

        Because product types have only one constructor, this will return 0 for every value of a product type.
